              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Excitation energies, mean lifetimes,",
                "gamma-ray branching ratios have been measured for",
                "levels bellow 5.3-MeV in Cl-37."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two large Ge(Li) detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cd-S, the sulphur content being enriched to 90% S-34,",
                "were used.",
                "For a gamma-gamma coincidence experiment were used",
                "the self-supporting Cd-S target 200 mug/cm**2 thick",
                "and was mounted 20-cm in front of a gold beam stop.",
                "The target for the polarization and lifetime experiment",
                "was  1-mg/cm**2 thick and was evaporated onto a thick",
                "gold backing.",
                "At recoil distance method -a different target was used",
                "for each run, their thicknesses being in the range 40-",
                "to 70-mug/cm**2 Cd(S) deposited onto 2 - to 3-mg/cm**2",
                "gold fils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A gamma-gamma coincidence experiment was",
                "performed at a bombarding energy of 11.5-MeV in order",
                "to clarify the decay scheme of Cl-37.",
                "Doppler shift attenuation method was used to determine",
                "the lifetimes of the levels, angular distribution and",
                "linear polarization.",
                "The lifetime of 3105-KeV, 4011-KeV, 4547-KeV and 5271-",
                "KeV level was measured by recoil distance method.",
                "In the angular correlation experiments the gamma-ray",
                "angular distribution were normalized using the isotopic",
                "1410-KeV gamma ray from the 1/2+-3/2+ transition in",
                "Ar-37. The 1/2+ level is populated at the same time",
                "in the S-34(a,ng)Ar-37 reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
